mage%20your%20iPhone%2C%26quot%3B%20Apple%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20giant%20also%20suggested%20avoiding%20using%20an%20external%20heat%20source%2C%20like%20hair%20dryers%20or%20compressed%20air%20to%20blow%20off%20liquid.%20Also%2C%20don't%20insert%20cotton%20swabs%20or%20paper%20towels%20into%20charging%20ports%20either%2C%20the%20tech%20giant%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Fen-us%2F102643%5C%22%3Eguidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Apple%20offered%20a%20few%20suggestions%20on%20what%20users%20can%20safely%20do%20when%20they%20get%20a%20%26quot%3Bliquid%20detected%26quot%3B%20on%20their%20phones.%20The%20company%20suggested%20tapping%20your%20phone%20against%20your%20hand%20with%20the%20connector%20pointing%20down%20to%20remove%20excess%20water%20from%20it.%20Then%2C%20just%20leave%20it%20in%20an%20area%20with%20good%20airflow%20to%20dry%20and%20wait%2030%20minutes%20before%20charging%20it.%20If%20the%20alert%20still%20pops%20up%2C%20leave%20the%20phone%20for%20another%20few%20minutes%20and%20just%20wait.%20It%20can%20take%20up%20to%2024%20hours%20to%20really%20get%20dry%20and%20users%20may%20see%20the%20liquid%20detection%20alert%20till%20that%20time%20frame%2C%20the%20company%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20you%20shouldn't%20charge%20your%20iPhone%20when%20it's%20wet%2C%20you%20might%20need%20to%20in%20an%20emergency.%20If%20you%20reconnect%20your%20iPhone%20to%20the%20cable%20or%20accessory%2C%20you%20have%20the%20option%20in%20an%20emergency%20to%20override%20the%20liquid%20detection%20and%20charge%20your%20iPhone.%26quot%3B%20Apple%20wrote%20in%20its%20advisory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20wireless%20charger%2C%20you%20can%20still%20use%20that%20to%20charge%20your%20iPhone.%20For%20best%20results%2C%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20back%20of%20your%20iPhone%20is%20dry%20before%20you%20place%20it%20on%20your%20Qi-certified%20charger%2C%26quot%3B%