%20December%201917%20after%20being%20torpedoed%20by%20a%20German%20submarine.%3Cp%3ENaval%20History%20and%20Heritage%20Command%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDivers%20retrieved%20a%20brass%20bell%20from%20the%20sunken%20USS%20Jacob%20Jones%2C%20a%20WW1-era%20American%20destroyer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bell%20was%20recovered%20due%20to%20concerns%20about%20the%20plundering%20of%20military%20wreck%20sites.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bell%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20Washington%20Navy%20Yard%20and%20held%20at%20the%20command's%20underwater%20archeology%20lab.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20century%20after%20a%20German%20U-boat%20torpedoed%20the%20USS%20Jacob%20Jones%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Britain%20during%20World%20War%20I%2C%20a%20team%20of%20divers%20retrieved%20the%20American%20destroyer's%20massive%20brass%20bell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20December%206%2C%201917%20%E2%80%94%20eight%20months%20after%20the%20US%20joined%20the%20fight%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Jacob%20Jones%20was%20attacked%20by%20a%20submarine%20off%20the%20southwest%20coast%20of%20Britain.%20It%20only%20took%20eight%20minutes%20for%20the%20large%20ship%20to%20sink%20entirely%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.usni.org%2F2024%2F02%2F12%2Frelic-recovered-from-u-s-destroyer-lost-in-wwi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Naval%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20killing%2064%20sailors%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ship%20would%20languish%20nearly%20400%20feet%20beneath%20the%20water's%20surface%20for%20more%20than%20100%20years%20before%20private%20divers%20discovered%20the%20wreck%20site%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Naval%20History%20and%20Heritage%20Command%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20spearheaded%20a%20diving%20mission%20to%20retrieve%20the%20Jacob%20Jones'%20giant%20brass%20bell%20from%20the%20depths%20earlier%20this%20year.%20A%20British%20government%20diving%20team%20was%20able%20to%20successfully%20raise%20