e's%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.apple.com%2Fen-us%2F102643%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupport%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%20discourages%20iPhone%20users%20from%20doing%20that%2C%20saying%20that%20small%20grains%20of%20rice%20could%20actually%20damage%20your%20phone%20if%2C%20say%2C%20particles%20get%20lodged%20into%20the%20ports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Apple%2C%20you%20also%20shouldn't%20try%20to%20dry%20your%20moist%20iPhone%20by%20inserting%20a%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20object%26quot%3B%20like%20a%20cotton%20swab%20or%20paper%20towel%20into%20the%20port%2C%20or%20use%20an%20external%20heat%20source%20like%20a%20blow%20dryer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20updated%20guidelines%20offer%20a%20few%20suggestions%20on%20what%20users%20can%20safely%20do.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20plug%20your%20iPhone%20into%20a%20wall%20outlet%20with%20a%20lightning%20accessory%20and%20a%20%26quot%3BLiquid%20Detected%26quot%3B%20alert%20appears%2C%20immediately%20unplug%20the%20cable%20from%20both%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20cable%20is%20disconnected%2C%20gently%20tap%20your%20iPhone%20against%20your%20hand%20with%20the%20port%20facing%20the%20floor%20to%20allow%20excess%20liquid%20to%20escape.%20After%20that%2C%20store%20the%20phone%20in%20a%20dry%20area%20where%20there's%20some%20airflow%20for%20at%20least%2030%20minutes%2C%20then%20try%20charging%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20liquid%20detection%20alert%20appears%20a%20second%20time%2C%20unplug%20and%20leave%20your%20phone%20to%20fully%20dry%20for%20up%20to%2024%20hours.%20After%20waiting%2C%20try%20charging%20the%20phone%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20phone%20still%20isn't%20charging%2C%20momentarily%20unplug%20the%20cable%20from%20the%20adapter%20and%20the%20adapter%20from%20the%20wall%2C%20then%20reconnect%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20all%20else%20fails%2C%20you%20may%20need%20to%20bring%20your%20iPhone%20to%20a%20repair%20shop%20or%2C%20at%20worst%2C%20consider%20get