20by%20Hate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recently%20published%20novel%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2023)%20by%20Nirmala%20Bhuradia%20depicts%20the%20horrendous%20implications%20of%20putting%20religion%20to%20the%20worst%20abuse%20in%20the%20pursuit%20of%20remorseless%20power%20politics.%20Bhuradia%20is%20an%20Indore-based%20fiction%20writer%20and%20journalist%20and%20a%20known%20name%20in%20the%20Hindi%20literary%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novel%20underlines%20that%20even%20decades%20after%20unprecedented%20brutalities%20and%20violence%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20partition%2C%20humanity%20seems%20to%20have%20refused%20to%20learn%20any%20lesson.%20The%20competitive%20communal%20politics%20aggravated%20by%20the%20colonial%20state%20and%20their%20global%20power%20politics%20ruined%20the%20subcontinent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20decades%2C%20the%20fury%20of%20communal%20hatred%20and%20violence%20has%20resurfaced%20in%20more%20horrendous%20forms%20across%20the%20subcontinent.%20Historian%20Papiya%20Ghosh%20(1958-2006)%20aptly%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Csubcontinental%20majoritarianism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20stands%20out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19181050%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-19-at-6.10.21-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22328%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697834%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22305%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECover%20photo%20of%20the%20book%20%E2%80%98Zeherkhurani%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20ask%20what%20is%20so%20fresh%20about%20the%20theme%20and%20treatment%20in%20this%20novel%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewhen%20there%20are%20many%20fictional%20books%20available%2C%20written%20by%20the%20tallest%20names%20in%20the%20Indian%20literary%20arena%20in%20different%20languages%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20in%20Urdu%2C%20Hindi%20and%20Punjabi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20existing%2C%20better%20known%20powerful%20stories%20(of%20Urdu%2C%20Hindi%20and%20Punjabi)%2C%20we%20hardly%20find%20the%20plight%20of%20Sindhi%20Hindu%20migrants%20who%20reside%20on%20our%20side%20of%20the%20border.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20the%20contemporary%20resurgence%20of%20hatred%2C%20violence%20and%20identity-politics%2C%20exacerbated%20much%20by%20the%20media%20and%20all%20pervasive%20social%20media%20is%20a%20novelty%20about%20the%20novel%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20theme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20treatment%20of%20the%20theme%20is%20dexterous.%20The%20story%20has%20been%20weaved%20brilliantly.%20The%20pains%20inflicted%20upon%20the%20many%20tragic%20characters%2C%20mostly%20women%20and%20some%20men%2C%20are%20something%20that%20the%20readers%20are%20bound%20to%20feel%20so%20very%20deeply%20and%20strongly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fin-a-world-of-borders-ones-search-for-a-home-can-tell-a-story%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20World%20of%20Borders%2C%20One%E2%80%99s%20Search%20for%20a%20Home%20Can%20Tell%20a%20Story%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Sindh%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20notable%20historical%20studies%20on%20the%20partition%20of%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20Sindh%20is%20concerned%20as%20a%20provincial%20territory%20which%20remained%20wholly%20with%20Pakistan%20unlike%20Punjab%20and%20Bengal.%20The%20Hindus%20of%20Sindh%20had%20to%20suffer%20either%20from%20the%20subjugation%20of%20the%20Muslim%20majoritarianism%20or%20had%20to%20migrate%20to%20parts%20which%20were%20to%20fall%20in%20India%20after%20August%2014-15%2C%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20%3Cem%3Egarm%20hawa%3C%2Fem%3E%20(hot%20air)%20of%20hatred%2C%20violence%2C%20rape%20and%20plunder%20blew%2C%20they%20were%20uprooted.%20Their%20journey%20from%20Karachi%20to%20Bombay%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20India%2C%20including%20Central%20India%20(Madhya%20Pradesh)%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20quite%20horrific.%20They%20were%20hardly%20familiar%20with%20places%20beyond%20their%20birthplace%20Sindh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20settlement%20within%20India%20made%20them%20realise%20that%20even%20among%20their%20own%20co-religionists%20they%20were%20mocked%2C%20marginalised%2C%20discriminated%2C%20and%20they%20were%20looked%20upon%20with%20contempt%20for%20their%20distinct%20language%2Fdialect%2C%20accents%2C%20culture%2C%20appearances%2C%20sartorial%20styles%2C%20etc.%20Their%20children%20studying%20in%20schools%20had%20to%20suffer%20from%20various%20kinds%20of%20segregation%20and%20ostracisation.%20Yet%2C%20they%20rebuilt%20their%20lives%20in%20trade%20and%20education%2C%20with%20their%20hard%20work%20and%20with%20dignity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESarah%20F.D.%20Ansari%E2%80%99s%20books%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20significant%20historical%20study%20on%20Sindh%20is%20highlighted%20by%20Sarah%20F.D.%20Ansari%20in%20her%20works.%20She%20wrote%20two%20books%20consecutively%20on%20late%20colonial%20and%20then%20on%20post-colonial%20period.%20These%20are%2C%20however%2C%20mostly%20on%20the%20Muslims%20who%20were%20(and%20are)%20anyway%20majority%20in%20the%20province.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnsari%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3ESufi%20Saints%20and%20State%20Power%3A%20The%20Pirs%20of%20Sind%2C%201843%E2%80%931947%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1992)%20examines%20the%20system%20of%20political%20control%20constructed%20by%20the%20British%20in%20Sind%20between%201843%20and%201947.%20She%20throws%20light%20on%20the%20local%20Muslim%20religious%20elite%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Epirs%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20hereditary%20%3Cem%3Esufi%3C%2Fem%3E%20saints%2C%20whose%20participation%20in%20the%20system%20ensured%20the%20politics%20of%20vivisecting%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%2C%20in%20particular.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3ELife%20After%20Partition%3A%20Migration%2C%20Community%20and%20Strife%20in%20Sindh%201947%20%E2%80%931962%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2005)%2C%20she%20examines%20the%20historical%20background%20%E2%80%93%20studying%20the%20years%20following%20partition%20%E2%80%93%20as%20ethnic%20politics%20had%20come%20to%20dominate%20Sindh%20by%20the%201990s%20with%20calls%20for%20Karachi%20to%20become%20a%20fifth%20province%20in%20its%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20stands%20out%20since%20it%20attempts%20to%20fill%20specific%20gaps%20of%20fictional%20articulation%20while%20historical%20exploration%20of%20the%20plight%20of%20the%20Sindhi%20Hindus%20among%20the%20Hindu%20majority%20of%20India%20is%20perhaps%20still%20awaited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20story%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20protagonist%20of%20the%20story%20is%20an%20inquisitive%20and%20interrogative%20girl%20Minali%20alias%20Minni%2C%20born%20in%201960%2C%20who%20grows%20up%20as%20a%20fiercely%20rational%20and%20a%20believer%20in%20pluralist%20coexistence.%20She%20chooses%20journalism%20as%20a%20profession%20which%20gets%20depressingly%20sallied%20by%20the%20time%20Minni%20and%20her%20husband%20reach%20their%2050s.%20Theirs%20is%20an%20almost%20lonely%20battle%20against%20the%20highly%20polarised%20society.%20The%20polarisation%20is%20because%20of%20many%20stereotypes%20against%20religious%20communities%2C%20fed%20mostly%20by%20communalised%20media%20owned%20by%20greedy%20corporates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinni%E2%80%99s%20cousin%2C%20Manohar%2C%20a%20hoodlum%2C%20lumpen%2C%20and%20eve-teaser%20grows%20up%20to%20become%20an%20important%20cadre%20of%20a%20communalised%20political%20party%20which%20eventually%20gets%20elected%20to%20power%2C%20riding%20on%20the%20wave%20of%20communal%20polarisation%2C%20hatred%20and%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManufacturing%20rumours%2C%20history%2C%20falsehood%20and%20concoctions%20are%20something%20his%20politics%20thrives%20on.%20Remarkably%2C%20Nirmala%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20the%20causation%20of%20partition%20is%20very%20good.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20rare%20novels%20in%20which%20the%20British%20culpability%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20partition%20has%20been%20brought%20out%20most%20clearly.%20For%20instance%2C%20when%20the%20British%20Governor%20of%20Punjab%20E.%20M.%20Jenkins%20(1896-1985)%20was%20frustrated%20by%20Khizr%20Hayat%20Khan%20Tiwana%E2%80%99s%20opposition%20to%20the%20partition%2C%20Tiwana%E2%80%99s%20government%20was%20toppled%20and%20the%20League%E2%80%99s%20was%20installed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImportant%20aspects%20highlighted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20shy%20away%20from%20highlighting%20the%20radicalisation%20of%20Pakistan%20in%20the%201970s%20and%201980s%2C%20internecine%20sectarian%20violence%20and%20absolute%20derailment%20of%20the%20economic%20progress%2C%20social%20fabric%20in%20tatters%2C%20as%20much%20as%20India%20is%20also%20increasingly%20becoming%20its%20mirror-image%2C%20transforming%20its%20republic%20into%20a%20theocracy.%20The%20fictional%20depiction%20acts%20as%20a%20reminder%20of%20the%20research%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fmodern-asian-studies%2Fissue%2F2E7479A370611ADC31E07FB07A01DBD3%5C%22%3Eessay%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20V.S.%20Kalra%20and%20Waqas%20Butt%2C%20%E2%80%98If%20I%20Speak%2C%20They%20Will%20Kill%20Me%2C%20to%20Remain%20Silent%20Is%20to%20Die%E2%80%99%3A%20Poetry%20of%20resistance%20in%20General%20Zia%E2%80%99s%20Pakistan%20(1977%E2%80%9388)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fmodern-asian-studies%2Fissue%2F2E7479A370611ADC31E07FB07A01DBD3%5C%22%3E(2019)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20during%20the%20very%20same%20decades%2C%20India%20too%20has%20been%20witnessing%20a%20consistent%20rise%20and%20expansion%20of%20identitarian%20forces.%20It%20resurged%20in%20the%20name%20of%20crusading%20against%20authoritarianism%20called%20Emergency.%20Some%20of%20these%20forces%20of%20resistance%20preferred%20to%20call%20themselves%20%E2%80%9CSmugglers%20of%20Truth%E2%80%9D%2C%20who%20found%20lots%20of%20support%20and%20funds%20from%20the%20expatriates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20the%20regressivism%20and%20bigotry%20of%20the%20affluent%20Non-Resident%20Indians%20(NRIs)%2C%20the%20scholar-journalist%20Arvind%20N%20Das%20(1949-2000)%20had%20once%20written%20a%20column%2C%20%E2%80%9CLong%20Distance%20Nationalism%E2%80%9D%20(%3Cem%3EFrontline%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20November%204%2C%201994).%20The%20expression%20is%20borrowed%20from%20Benedict%20Anderson%E2%80%99s%201983%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EImagined%20Communities%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20roles%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CSmugglers%20of%20Truth%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20exposed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fmodern-asian-studies%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fsmugglers-of-truth-the-indian-diaspora-hindu-nationalism-and-the-emergency-197577%2F2C59B29D6C36D0CA7C8B1C2EE207534D%5C%22%3Erecent%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2018).%20The%20rapid%20communalisation%20culminated%20into%20the%20anti-Sikh%20riots%20of%201984%20and%20ever%20since%20then%2C%20bigotry%2C%20hatred%2C%20strife%20and%20pogroms%20kept%20becoming%20more%20a%20socio-political%20mainstream%20than%20a%20margin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novel%20%3Cem%3EZeherkhurani%3C%2Fem%3E%20possibly%20attempts%20to%20pin%20hope%20of%20a%20good%20future%20on%20the%20rationalist-pluralist%20women%20(and%20men)%20intelligentsia%20and%20journalists.%20This%20optimism%2C%20though%20not%20misplaced%2C%20needs%20some%20quantum%20of%20reservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20educated%20middle%20classes%20and%20the%20affluent%20ones%20are%20not%20necessarily%20committed%20to%20humanitarianism%20and%20justice.%20Greed%20for%20name%2C%20fame%2C%20pelf%20and%20power%20of%20these%20classes%20across%20the%20globe%20has%20pushed%20the%20world%20into%20the%20vortex%20of%20bigotry%2C%20fanaticism%2C%20hatred%20and%20violence.%20This%20has%20aggravated%20in%20recent%20decades%20even%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Byung-Chul%20Han%E2%80%99s%20recent%20book(let)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Ffan-publication%2Fanti-networks-and-a-review-of-byung-chan-hans-psychopolitics-6c2ada673bb2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPsychopolitics%2520is%2520a%2520fascinating%2520and%2Cproductive%252C%2520useful%2520strategy%2520or%2520platforms.%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPsychopolitics%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cis%20a%20fascinating%20and%20well-written%20treatise%20on%20subjects%20that%20feel%20beaten%20to%20death%2C%20and%20is%20situated%20within%20a%20radical%20culture%20seemingly%20damned%20to%20futility%20by%20capitalist%20realism%20and%20one%20incapable%20of%20generating%20productive%2C%20useful%20strategy%20or%20platforms%E2%80%9D%20of%20resistance%20and%20solidarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiction%20writers%20may%20derive%20creative%20insights%20from%20such%20works%20capturing%20the%20harsh%20realities%20of%20our%20times.%20Bhuradia%20is%20one%20such%20fiction%20writer%20of%20our%20times%20who%20is%20engaged%20in%20the%20pursuit%20of%20fictional%20articulation%20of%20the%20contemporary%20horrors%20of%20humans%20against%20fellow%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20critical%20observations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20seven%20chapters%20of%20the%20novel%2C%20depicting%20the%20recent%20decades%2C%20have%20become%20a%20little%20less%20creative%20in%20terms%20of%20artistic%20finesse.%20Nonetheless%2C%20the%20novel%20does%20hold%20a%20mirror%20before%20all%20of%20us%20about%20the%20way%20we%20are%2C%20as%20of%20now%2C%20and%20what%20we%20are%20likely%20to%20become%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20work%20towards%20rescuing%20the%20pluralist%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novel%20seems%20to%20be%20concerned%20with%20depicting%20only%20the%20minorities%2C%20including%20the%20minorities%20within%20the%20minorities.%20Thus%2C%20Sindhi%20Hindu%20families%20on%20the%20margins%20of%20Hindu%20majority%20society%2C%20Bohras%20among%20the%20Muslims%2C%20with%20their%20own%20regressive%20cultural%20practices%20and%20subjugation%20of%20women%2C%20all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20a%20particular%20version%20of%20religion%2C%20and%20the%20Sikhs%20find%20their%20stories%20of%20suffering%20in%20this%20novel.%20Dalits%20left%20in%20Pakistan%20too%20have%20found%20a%20mention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eventual%20disintegration%20of%20the%20once%20vivacious%20Mangal%20Bhawan%20and%20the%20Fatima%20Manzil%2C%20find%20a%20brilliant%20creative%20articulation.%20Intra-community%20oppressions%20(and%20horrific%20patriarchy%20perpetuating%20with%20growing%20superstitions)%20against%20the%20rationalists%20and%20pluralists%20are%20the%20running%20themes%20in%20the%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state-%20(and%20religion-)%20driven%20feeding%20of%20communal%20poison%20is%20a%20running%20theme%20throughout%20the%20story%20and%20stories%20within%20the%20story%20of%20the%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-nilanjana-sengupta-chickpeas-singapore%5C%22%3EThe%20Gods%20in%20Our%20Kitchens%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20emotional%20aspect%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20highlights%20how%20polarisation%2C%20madness%2C%20violence%20and%20tremendous%20brutalities%20make%20victims%20mentally%20sick.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20character%20of%20the%20child%20Banta%20is%20written%20in%20such%20a%20manner%20that%20it%20will%20make%20readers%20cry%20on%20multiple%20occasions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanta%2C%20separated%20from%20his%20parents%2C%20is%20subjected%20to%20mutilations%20and%20torture%20several%20times.%20Each%20time%20the%20boy%20is%20made%20to%20change%20his%20religious%20identity%2C%20he%20is%20face%20to%20face%20with%20the%20rioters%20of%20the%20rival%20identity.%20Even%20his%20part%20pretension%20and%20part%20reality%20of%20having%20become%20dumb%2C%20or%20resorting%20to%20become%20luminal%20in%20identitarian%20terms%20(such%20as%20chanting%20Bulley%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20poetry%3A%20%3Cem%3EBulleyh%20Kih%20Jaana%20Main%20Kaun%3C%2Fem%3E)%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20ensure%20his%20safety%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20violent%20religious%20orthodoxy%20of%20various%20hues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20despite%20having%20been%20circumcised%2C%20his%20Sikh%20identity%20gets%20revealed%20and%20he%20ends%20up%20losing%20even%20the%20circumcised%20organ%20altogether.%20With%20this%20horrific%20loss%2C%20he%20does%20get%20re-united%20with%20his%20father%2C%20who%20has%20already%20abandoned%20his%20mother%2C%20as%20she%20was%20abducted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMental%20illness%20has%20been%20inflicted%20upon%20such%20victims%20by%20the%20society.%20With%20such%20characters%20in%20the%20story%2C%20one%20is%20reminded%20of%20Michel%20Focault%E2%80%99s%201961%20edition%20of%20the%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EMadness%20and%20Civilization%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20wherein%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CModern%20man%20no%20longer%20communicates%20with%20the%20madman%20%E2%80%A6%20There%20is%20no%20common%20language%2C%20or%20rather%2C%20it%20no%20longer%20exists%3B%20the%20constitution%20of%20madness%20as%20mental%20illness%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%2018th%20century%2C%20bears%20witness%20to%20a%20rupture%20in%20a%20dialogue%2C%20gives%20the%20separation%20as%20already%20enacted%2C%20and%20expels%20from%20the%20memory%20all%20those%20imperfect%20words%2C%20of%20no%20fixed%20syntax%2C%20spoken%20falteringly%2C%20in%20which%20the%20exchange%2C%20between%20madness%20and%20reason%2C%20was%20carried%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20novel%20is%20not%20only%20about%20the%20darker%20aspects.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20fail%20to%20capture%20the%20anecdotes%20of%20people%20rising%20against%20the%20violence%20and%20hatred%20and%20helping%20their%20neighbourhood%20defying%20the%20politically%20foisted%20religious%20divides%20and%20polarisation.%20Such%20characters%20and%20anecdotes%20give%20a%20little%20respite%20from%20the%20horrific%20sufferings%20of%20the%20humans%20that%20runs%20through%20the%20story%20and%20it%20also%20offers%20hope%20that%20such%20dark%20phases%20shall%20pass%20away%20sooner%20than%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20novel%20is%20a%20diagnosis%20of%20and%20a%20very%20damning%20charge-sheet%20against%20the%20crime%20of%20hatred%20and%20violence%20being%20committed%20by%20humans%20against%20humans%20in%20our%20times.%20It%E2%80%99s%20definitely%20a%20must-read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fmohammad-sajjad%5C%22%3EMohammad%20Sajjad%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20History%20at%20Aligarh%20Muslim%20University%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0Muslim%20Politics%20in%20Bihar%3A%20Changing%20Contours.%20He%20tweets%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsajjadhist%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3E%40sajjadhist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708432195000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fzeherkhurani-nirmala-bhuradias-latest-novel-holds-mirror-to-our-times-consumed-by-hate%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20Hindi%20novel%20underlines%20that%20even%20decades%20after%20unprecedented%20brutalities%20and%20violence%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20partition%2C%20humanity%20seems%20to%20have%20refused%20to%20learn%20any%20lesson.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fzeherkhurani-nirmala-bhuradias-latest-novel-holds-mirr