s%3D1200_630%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstarbucks-union-elections_n_65d24123e4b0ce1bdc39d7d5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20union%20Workers%20United%20has%20organized%20roughly%20400%20stores%2C%20but%20is%20locked%20in%20a%20bitter%20bargaining%20fight%20with%20the%20coffee%20chain.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A287%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstarbucks-union-elections_n_65d24123e4b0ce1bdc39d7d5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-huffpost-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstarbucks-union-elections_n_65d24123e4b0ce1bdc39d7d5%2Famp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fstarbucks-union-elections_n_65d24123e4b0ce1bdc39d7d5%2Famp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Of%20Magic%20Beans%20and%20Modified%20Mustard%3A%20How%20GMOs%20Will%20Destroy%20Indian%20Agriculture%20and%20Impact%20Health%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20154101%2Fdietmar-kraus-qtgR-PgjVV4-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EHybrid%20Bt%20cotton%2C%20the%20only%20commercialised%20Genetically%20Modified%20crop%20in%20India%2C%20has%20failed%20conclusively.%20Based%20on%20this%20failure%20and%20the%20evidence%20of%20the%20clear%20harm%20that%20GM%20Organisms%20(GMOs)%20will%20cause%20to%20human%20and%20animal%20health%2C%20the%20Union%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20to%20commercialise%20herbicide-tolerant%20(HT)%20mustard%20will%20destroy%20not%20just%20Indian%20mustard%20agriculture%2C%20but%20citizens%E2%80%99%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJanuary%20witnessed%20five%20days%20of%20intense%20hearings%20on%20this%20matter%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(SC)%20%E2%80%94%20the%20GMO%20Public%20Interest%20Writ%20filed%20almost%2020%20years%20ago%20in%202005%20by%20the%20author%2C%20which%20ended%20on%20January%2018%2C%202024.%20In%20these%20last%2020%20years%2C%20piecemeal%20hearings%20have%20dealt%20with%20submissions%20relating%20to%20individual%20crops%20like%20hybrid%20Bt%20cotton%2C%20the%20attempted%20commercialisation%20of%20hybrid%20Bt%20brinjal%20(2010)%20and%20now%20the%20attempt%20to%20commercialise%20hybrid%20HT%20mustard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20provided%20here%20is%20a%20distillation%20of%20the%20critical%20inputs%20of%20those%2060%2B%20submissions%20based%20on%20the%20affidavits%20and%20studies%20of%20leading%2C%20independent%20scientists%20and%20experts%20of%20international%20renown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20is%20a%20serious%20and%20proven%20conflict%20of%20interest%20among%20our%20regulators%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Agriculture%20along%20with%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Agricultural%20Research%20(ICAR)%2C%20which%20promote%20GMOs%20in%20Indian%20agriculture.%20This%20evidence%20reflects%20in%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20TEC%20Report%20(Technical%20Expert%20Committee)%20appointed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(SC)%20in%202012%20and%20two%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committees%20of%202012%20and%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Modern%20biotechnology%E2%80%99%20or%20genetically%20modified%20organisms%20(GMOs)%20are%20products%20where%20the%20genomes%20of%20organisms%20are%20transformed%20through%20laboratory%20techniques%2C%20including%20genetically%20engineered%20DNA%20(recombinant)%20and%20its%20direct%20introduction%20into%20cells.%20These%20are%20techniques%20not%20used%20in%20traditional%20breeding%20and%20selection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGMOs%20create%20organisms%20in%20ways%20that%20have%20never%20existed%20in%203.8%20billion%20years%20of%20evolution%20and%20produce%20%E2%80%98unintended%20effects%E2%80%99%20that%20are%20not%20immediately%20apparent.%20This%20is%20why%20rigorous%2C%20independent%20protocols%20for%20risk%20and%20hazard%20identification%20are%20the%20sine%20qua%20non%20of%20correct%20regulation%20in%20the%20public%20interest.%20The%20Indian%20%E2%80%98Rules%20of%201989%E2%80%99%20%5BRules%20for%20the%20Manufacture%2FUse%2FImport%2FExport%20and%20Storage%20of%20Hazardous%20Microorganisms%2F%20Genetically%20Engineered%20Organisms%20or%20Cells%2C%201989%E2%80%9D%20under%20the%20Environment%20(Protection)%20Act%2C%201986%5D%20describe%20GMOs%20as%20%E2%80%9Chazardous%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20outstanding%20concern%20is%20contamination%20of%20the%20natural%20environment%20(including%20the%20cross-transfer%20of%20pollen%20by%20bees%20to%20wild%20or%20other%20domestic%20crop%20varieties)%20by%20GMOs%3B%20a%20worry%20that%20the%20Convention%20on%20Biological%20Diversity%20%E2%80%93%20which%20India%20is%20a%20signatory%20to%20%E2%80%93%20also%20recognises.%20India%20is%20one%20of%2017%20listed%20international%20hotspots%20of%20diversity%2C%20which%20includes%20mustard%2C%20brinjal%20and%20rice.%20India%20is%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biological%20diversity%20in%20brinjal%2C%20with%20over%202%2C500%20varieties%20grown%20in%20the%20country%20and%20as%20many%20as%2029%20wild%20species.%20India%20is%20also%20a%20secondary%20centre%20of%20origin%20of%20rape-seed%20mustard%20with%20over%209%2C000%20accessions%20in%20our%20gene%20bank%20(National%20Bureau%20of%20Plant%20Genetic%20Resources).%20With%20a%20commercialised%20GM%20crop%2C%20contamination%20is%20certain.%20The%20precautionary%20principle%20must%20apply%2C%20is%20read%20into%20the%20Constitution%20and%20is%20a%20legal%20precedent%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHybrid%20Bt%20cotton%20was%20introduced%20in%202002%20and%20remains%20the%20only%20approved%20commercialised%20crop%20in%20India.%20It%20has%20been%20an%20abject%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFailure%20of%20Bt%20cotton%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20the%20only%20country%20in%20the%20world%20to%20have%20introduced%20the%20Bt%20gene%20into%20hybrid%20Bt%20Cotton.%C2%A0%20It%20was%20introduced%20in%20hybrids%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98value-capture%20mechanism%E2%80%99%2C%20according%20to%20K.R.%20Kranthi%2C%20a%20professor%20with%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20of%20research%20in%20cotton%20who%20was%20also%20the%20former%20director%20of%20the%20Central%20Institute%20for%20Cotton%20Research%20(CICR).%20The%20hybrid%20technology%20disallows%20seed%20saving%20by%20millions%20of%20small%20farmers.%20Conservative%20estimates%20indicate%20that%20Indian%20farmers%20may%20have%20paid%20an%20additional%20amount%20of%20Rs%2014%2C000%20crore%20for%20Bt%20cotton%20seeds%20between%202002%20and%202018%2C%20of%20which%20trait%20fees%20(an%20amount%20paid%20to%20developers%20of%20the%20seeds%20for%20using%20their%20technology)%20alone%20amounted%20to%20Rs%207%2C337.37%20crore%2C%20said%20Kranthi.%20There%20was%20also%20a%20phenomenal%20three-fold%20increase%20in%20labour%20costs%20in%20hybrid%20cotton%20cultivation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Gutierrez%2C%20Professor%20Emeritus%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Environmental%20Science%2C%20Policy%20and%20Management%20in%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20is%20among%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20leading%20entomologists%20and%20cotton%20scientists.%20He%20provided%20the%20ecological%20explanation%20of%20why%20hybrid%20Bt%20cotton%20is%20every%20bit%20a%20disaster%20that%20it%20is%20in%20India.%20Most%20hybrid%20cottons%20are%20long%20season%20(180-200-day%20duration).%20This%20increases%20the%20opportunities%20for%20pest%20resurgence%20and%20outbreaks%20because%20it%20links%20into%20the%20lifecycle%20of%20the%20pest.%20The%20low-density%20planting%20also%20increases%20the%20cost%20of%20hybrid%20seeds%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHybrids%20require%20stable%20water%20too%20(therefore%2C%20irrigation%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20rain-fed)%20and%20more%20fertiliser.%20Some%2090%25%20of%20current%20Bt%20cotton%20hybrids%20appear%20susceptible%20to%20sap-sucking%20insects%2C%20leaf-curl%20virus%20and%20leaf%20reddening%2C%20adding%20to%20input%20costs%20and%20loss%20of%20yield.%20Most%20telling%20is%20that%20India%20produces%20only%203.3%20million%20tonnes%20from%20its%20irrigated%20area%20of%204.9%20million%20hectares%20compared%20to%206.96%20million%20tonnes%20from%20an%20equivalent%20area%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHybrid%20Bt%20cotton%20in%20India%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20yield%20plateau%2C%20high%20production%20costs%20and%20low%20productivity%20that%20reduce%20farmer%20revenues%2C%20correlated%20with%20increased%20farmer%20distress%20and%20suicides.%20It%20has%20stymied%20the%20development%20of%20economically%20viable%20high-density%20short-season%20(HD-SS)%20Non-Bt%20high-yielding%20straight-line%20varieties.%20The%20failure%20of%20hybrid%20Bt%20cotton%20is%20an%20abject%20lesson%20for%20GMO%20implementation%20in%20other%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20regulators%20attempted%20to%20repeat%20history%20in%20the%20form%20of%20hybrid%20Bt%20brinjal%20and%20hybrid%20HT%20mustard.%20This%2C%20despite%20field%20trial%20solutions%20(CICR%20data)%20of%20high-density%20short-season%20(HD-SS)%20NON-GMO%20pure-line%20(non-hybrid)%2C%20rainfed%20cotton%20varieties%20being%20developed%20in%20India%20that%20could%20more%20than%20double%20yield%20and%20nearly%20triple%20net%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20admitted%20in%20its%20affidavit%20in%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20(January%2022%2C%202016)%2C%20adding%2C%20(on%20January%2023%2C%202017)%2C%20that%20Bt%20%E2%80%9Ccotton%20seeds%20are%20now%20unaffordable%20to%20farmers%20due%20to%20high%20royalties%20charged%20by%20MMBL%20(Mahyco%20Monsanto%20Biotech%20Ltd)%20which%20has%20a%20near%20monopoly%20on%20Bt%20cotton%20seeds%20and%20that%20this%20has%20led%20to%20a%20market%20failure%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20there%20is%20no%20trait%20for%20yield%20enhancement%20in%20the%20Bt%20technology.%20Any%20intrinsic%20yield%20increase%20is%20properly%20attributable%20to%20its%20hybridisation%20in%20both%20Bt%20cotton%20and%20Bt%20brinjal.%20Lower%20insecticide%20use%20is%20the%20reason%20for%20introducing%20the%20Bt%20technology%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pink%20bollworm%20has%20developed%20high%20levels%20of%20resistance%20against%20Bollgard-II%20Bt%20cotton%2C%20leading%20to%20increased%20insecticide%20usage%20in%20India%2C%20increases%20in%20new%20induced%20secondary%20pests%20and%20crop%20failures.%20The%20annual%20report%202015-16%20of%20the%20ICAT-CICR%20confirms%20that%20Bt%20cotton%20is%20no%20longer%20effective%20for%20bollworm%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInsecticide%20usage%20on%20cotton%20in%202002%20was%200.88%20kg%20per%20hectare%2C%20which%20increased%20to%200.97%20kg%20per%20hectare%20in%202013%20(Srivastav%20and%20Kolady%202016).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMatters%20were%20deliberately%20muddied%20in%20India%2C%20leading%20to%20any%20hybrid%20vigour%20being%20attributed%20to%20the%20Bt%20technology!%20Yields%20have%20stagnated%20despite%20the%20deployment%20of%20all%20available%20latest%20technologies%2C%20including%20the%20introduction%20of%20new%20potent%20GM%20technologies%2C%20a%20two-fold%20increase%20in%20the%20use%20of%20fertilisers%20and%20increased%20insecticide%20use%20and%20irrigation.%20And%20yet%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20global%20rank%20is%2030-32nd%20in%20terms%20of%20yield.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%2013%20years%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20increased%20302%25.%20In%2015%20years%2C%20there%20was%20a%20450%25%20increase%20in%20labour%20costs.%20The%20costs%20of%20hybrid%20seed%2C%20insecticide%20and%20fertiliser%20increased%20more%20than%20250%20to%20300%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20profit%20for%20farmers%20was%20Rs.%205971%2Fha%20in%202003%20(pre-Bt)%20but%20plummeted%20to%20net%20losses%20of%20Rs%206%2C286%20in%202015%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feands.dacnet.nic.in%2FCost_of_Cultivation.htm%2520Cost%2520of%2520cultivation%2520%2F%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20Kranthi%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERegulatory%20failure%3A%20Bt%20brinjal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegulators%20tried%20to%20commercialise%20Bt%20brinjal%20and%20its%20hybrids%20in%202009.%20The%20Bt%20gene%20is%20proven%20to%20be%20undeniably%20toxic%20(experts%20including%20David%20Schubert%2C%20former%20professor%20and%20head%20of%20the%20Cellular%20Neurobiology%20Laboratory%20at%20the%20Salk%20Institute%20for%20Biological%20Studies%20in%20La%20Jolla%2C%20CA%3B%20Arpad%20Pusztai%2C%20former%20professor%20at%20the%20Rowett%20Research%20Institute%20in%20Aberdeen%3B%20Gilles-%C3%89ric%20S%C3%A9ralini%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20molecular%20biology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Caen%2C%20France%20and%20others%20have%20confirmed%20this).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202008%2C%20the%20regulators%20were%20forced%20to%20publish%20the%20developers%E2%80%99%20(Monsanto-Mahyco)%20self-assessed%20bio-safety%20dossier%20on%20their%20website%2C%2016%20months%20after%20the%20order%20of%20the%20SC%20to%20make%20the%20safety%20dossier%20data%20public%20(February%2015%2C%202007).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBt%20brinjal%20was%20the%20first%20vegetable%20food%20crop%20in%20the%20world%20to%20be%20approved%20for%20commercialisation%2C%20by%20the%20collective%20regulatory%20body%20and%20their%20expert%20committees%2C%20virtually%20without%20oversight.%20When%20the%20international%20scientific%20community%20examined%20the%20raw%20data%2C%20their%20collective%20comments%20were%20scathing.%20Jack%20Heinemann%2C%20Professor%20of%20Molecular%20Biology%20and%20Genetics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Canterbury%20stated%20that%20Mahyco%20has%20failed%20at%20the%20first%2C%20elementary%20step%20of%20the%20safety%20study%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20never%20seen%20less%20professionalism%20in%20the%20presentation%20and%20quality%20assurance%20of%20molecular%20data%20than%20in%20this%20study%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20criticised%20Mahyco%20for%20using%20outdated%20studies%2C%20testing%20to%20below%20acceptable%20standards%20and%20using%20inappropriate%20and%20invalid%20test%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20comprehensive%20critique%20of%20Monsanto%E2%80%99s%20Dossier%20%E2%80%98Bt%20brinjal%20Event%20EE1%E2%80%99%2C%20David%20Andow%20%E2%80%93%20a%20Distinguished%20McKnight%20University%20Professor%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Entomology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Minnesota%20%E2%80%93%20listed%2037%20studies%20of%20which%20perhaps%20one%20had%20been%20conducted%20and%20reported%20to%20a%20satisfactory%20level%20by%20Monsanto.%20He%20concluded%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20GEAC%20set%20too%20narrow%20a%20scope%20for%20environmental%20risk%20assessment%20(ERA)%20of%20hybrid%20Bt%20brinjal%2C%20and%20it%20is%20because%20of%20this%20overly%20narrow%20scope%20that%20the%20EC-II%20is%20not%20an%20adequate%20ERA%E2%80%A6%20most%20of%20the%20possible%20environmental%20risks%20of%20Bt%20brinjal%20have%20not%20been%20adequately%20evaluated%3B%20this%20includes%20risks%20to%20local%20varieties%20of%20brinjal%20and%20wild%20relatives%2C%20risks%20to%20biological%20diversity%2C%20and%20risk%20of%20resistance%20evolution%20in%20BFSB.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Central%20government%20itself%20declared%20an%20unconditional%20and%20indefinite%20moratorium%20on%20Bt%20brinjal%20in%20February%202009%20based%20on%20the%20collective%20responses%20of%20the%20scientific%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisaster%20in%20the%20making%3A%20GM%20Hybrid%20HT%20Mustard%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20Bt%2C%20HT%20is%20a%20pesticidal%20crop%20(to%20kill%20weeds).%20These%20two%20GMO%20technologies%20represent%20about%2098%25%20of%20crops%20planted%20worldwide%2C%20with%20HT%20crops%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%2080%25.%20Neither%20has%20a%20trait%20for%20yield.%20In%20its%202002%20Report%2C%20the%20United%20States%20Department%20for%20Agriculture%20stated%3A%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Ccurrently%20available%20GM%20crops%20do%20not%20increase%20the%20yield%20potential%E2%80%A6%20In%20fact%2C%20yield%20may%20even%20decrease%20if%20the%20%3Cu%3Evarieties%20%3C%2Fu%3Eused%20to%20carry%20the%20herbicide%20tolerant%20or%20insect-resistant%20genes%20are%20not%20the%20highest%20yielding%20cultivars%E2%80%A6%20Perhaps%20the%20biggest%20issue%20raised%20by%20these%20results%20is%20how%20to%20explain%20the%20rapid%20adoption%20of%20GE%20crops%20when%20farm%20financial%20impacts%20appear%20to%20be%20mixed%20or%20even%20negative.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20developer%E2%80%99s%20(Centre%20for%20Genetic%20Manipulation%20of%20Crop%20Plants%20University%20of%20Delhi)%20bio-safety%20dossier%2C%20in%20contempt%20of%20the%20SC%20orders%2C%20has%20never%20made%20its%20data%20public.%20A%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20request%20was%20filed%20in%202016%20with%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Rape-Seed%20Mustard%20Research%2C%20which%20conducts%20protocols%20of%20non-GMO%20mustard%20trials%20for%20crop%20improvement%20programmes%20for%20our%20farmers%2C%20for%20varietal%20stability%20and%20performance.%20The%20RTI%20was%20an%20eye%20opener.%20Virtually%20all%20the%20directorate%E2%80%99s%20norms%20were%20flouted%20in%20the%20field%20trials%2C%20making%20them%20invalid.%20Hybrid%20mustard%20HT%20DMH%2011%20was%20out-yielded%20by%20more%20than%20the%2010%25%20norm%20by%20non-GMO%20varieties%20and%20hybrids%2C%20which%20forced%20the%20developers%20to%20admit%20this%20fact%20in%20their%20formal%20reply%20affidavit%20in%20the%20SC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHybrid%20HT%20mustard%20DMH%2011%20employs%20three%20transgenes%3A%20the%20male%20sterility%20gene%2C%20barnase%2C%20the%20female%20restorer%20gene%2C%20barstar%2C%20and%20the%20bar%20gene%20that%20confers%20tolerance%20to%20Bayer%E2%80%99s%20herbicide%20glufosinate%20ammonium%20or%20basta.%20Each%20of%20the%20parent%20lines%20has%20the%20bar%20gene%20that%20makes%20them%20both%20HT%20crops%20along%20with%20their%20resulting%20hybrid%20DMH%2011.%20The%20reason%20for%20employing%20barnase%20and%20barstar%20is%20because%20mustard%20is%20a%20closed%20pollinating%20crop%20(even%20though%20it%20out%20crosses%20pretty%20well%2C%2018%25%2B)%20and%20this%20technology%20(a%20male%20sterility%20technology)%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20produce%20mustard%20hybrids.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20hybrid%20technology.%20Its%20counterpart%20in%20non-GMO%20male%20sterility%20technology%20is%20the%20CMS%20system%20(cytoplasmic%20male%20sterility).%20Employing%20male%20sterility%20in%20mustard%20allows%20it%20to%20be%20used%20more%20easily%20in%20already%20existing%20hybridisation%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20curious%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20the%20regulators%20have%20tried%20to%20obfuscate%20the%20facts%20and%20muddy%20the%20waters.%20Their%20first%20response%20was%20that%20the%20acronym%20HT%20in%20mustard%20DMH%2011%20means%20%E2%80%98hybrid%20technology%E2%80%99.%20When%20this%20didn%E2%80%99t%20work%2C%20the%20next%20%E2%80%98try%E2%80%99%20was%20that%20DMH%2011%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20HT%20crop!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20too%20was%20easily%20proved%20wrong%20because%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20bar%20gene.%20Now%2C%20this%20fact%20has%20been%20admitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20regulators%20have%20failed%20either%20intentionally%2C%20or%20because%20they%20are%20simply%20unable%20to%20stop%20illegal%20(unapproved%20by%20the%20regulator)%20HT%20Bt%20cotton%20being%20grown%20on%20a%20commercial%20scale%20for%20the%20last%2015%20years%20or%20so.%20This%20is%20the%20state%20of%20GMO%20regulation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBayer%E2%80%99s%20own%20data%20sheet%20states%20that%20glufosinate%20causes%20birth%20defects%20and%20is%20damaging%20to%20most%20plants%20that%20it%20comes%20into%20contact%20with.%20Like%20its%20counterpart%20glyphosate%2C%20it%20is%20a%20systemic%2C%20broad%20spectrum%2C%20non-selective%20herbicide%20(it%20indiscriminately%20kills%20soil%20organisms%2C%20beneficial%20insects%20etc)%20and%20is%20damaging%20to%20most%20plants%20and%20aquatic%20life.%20The%20US%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20classifies%20glufosinate%20ammonium%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpersistent%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cmobile%E2%80%9D%20and%20is%20%E2%80%9Cexpected%20to%20adversely%20affect%20non-target%20terrestrial%20plant%20species%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlufosinate%20is%20not%20permitted%20in%20crop%20plants%20in%20India%2C%20under%20the%20Insecticides%20Act%20(1968).%20Since%20it%20is%20very%20persistent%20in%20the%20environment%2C%20it%20will%20certainly%20contaminate%20water%20supplies%20in%20addition%20to%20food.%20Surfactants%20are%20used%20to%20get%20the%20active%20ingredients%20into%20the%20plant%2C%20which%20is%20engineered%20to%20withstand%20the%20herbicide%2C%20so%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20die%20when%20sprayed.%20The%20herbicide%20and%20surfactant%20are%20sprayed%20directly%20on%20the%20crops%20and%20significant%20quantities%20are%20then%20taken%20up%20into%20the%20plant.%C2%A0%20The%20weeds%20die%20%E2%80%94%20or%20used%20to!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Geological%20survey%20noted%20that%20while%2020%20million%20pounds%2Fyear%20of%20glyphosate%20was%20used%20prior%20to%20GE%20crops%20(1992)%2C%20280%20million%20pounds%2Fyear%20was%20used%20in%202012%2C%20largely%20as%20a%20result%20of%20glyphosate-resistant%20crops.%20In%20the%20U.S.%20alone%2C%20glyphosate-resistant%20weeds%20were%20estimated%20to%20occupy%20an%20area%20of%20over%2024%20million%20hectares%20as%20of%202012.%20This%20is%20a%20failed%20and%20unsustainable%20technology%20anywhere%2C%20and%20for%20India%20it%20will%20be%20disastrous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stated%20objective%20by%20the%20regulators%20themselves%20for%20HT%20mustard%20is%20that%20the%20two%20HT%20parent%20lines%20(barnase%20and%20barstar%20each%20with%20the%20bar%20gene)%2C%20will%20be%20similarly%20employed%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20best%20(non-GMO)%20varieties%20to%20create%20new%20crosses%20resulting%20in%20any%20number%20of%20HT%20hybrid%20mustard%20DMH%20crops.%20Thus%2C%20Indian%20mustard%20varieties%20(non-GMO)%20in%20a%20very%20short%20time%20will%20be%20contaminated%20and%20Indian%20mustard%20agriculture%20(which%20is%20non-GMO)%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20regulators%20claim%20that%20GMO%20HT%20hybrid%20DMH%2011%20will%20create%20a%20significant%20dent%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20oilseeds%20imports.%20Given%20that%20GMO%20mustard%20has%20no%20gene%20for%20yield%20enhancement%20and%20is%20significantly%20out-yielded%20by%20non-GMO%20mustard%20hybrids%20and%20varieties%2C%20this%20is%20indeed%20a%20magic%20bean%20produced%20from%20thin%20air%20by%20the%20regulators%2C%20defying%20all%20logic%20and%20commonsense.%20Mustard%20oil%20imports%20are%20virtually%20zero%20(ie%20rapeseed%20mustard%20as%20distinct%20from%20canola%20rape%20oil%20which%20is%20also%20illegal%20GMO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20current%20steep%20decline%20in%20oilseeds%20production%20in%20Indian%20farming%20must%20be%20laid%20at%20the%20door%20of%20a%20wrong%20policy%20decision%20that%20comprehensively%20ignored%20national%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20interest%20to%20severely%20slash%20import%20duties%20on%20oilseeds%20of%20around%20300%25%20to%20virtually%20zero.%20In%201993-94%2C%20India%20imported%20just%203%25%20of%20our%20oil-seed%20demand%3B%20we%20were%20self-%20sufficient.%20Then%20we%20happily%20bowed%20to%20pressure%20from%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%20and%20now%20import%20almost%2070%25%20of%20our%20demand%20in%20edible%20oils%2C%20as%20per%20policy%20analyst%20Devinder%20Sharma.%20This%20is%20the%20real%20reason%20for%20our%20heavy%20import%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20TEC%20recommends%20a%20double%20bar%20on%20GM%20Mustard%20%E2%80%94%20for%20being%20an%20HT%20crop%20and%20also%20in%20a%20centre%20of%20mustard%20diversification%20and%2For%20origin.%20I%20hope%20that%20our%20government%20will%20recognise%20the%20dangers%20of%20GMOs%2C%20bar%20HT%20crops%20including%20GM%20mustard%2C%20and%20impose%20a%20moratorium%20on%20all%20Bt%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAruna%20Rodrigues%20is%20the%20Lead%20Petitioner%20in%20the%20GMO%20PIL%20filed%20in%202005%20for%20a%20moratorium%20on%20GM%20crops.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708430440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20154101%2Fdietmar-kraus-qtgR-PgjVV4-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fof-magic-beans-and-modified-mustard-how-gmos-will-destroy-indian-agriculture-and-impact-health%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20introduction%20of%20Bt%20and%20HT%20crops%20will%20harm%20the%20health%20of%201%20billion%20Indians%20and%20their%20animals.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fof-magic-beans-and-modified-mustard-how-gmos-will-destroy-indian-agriculture-and-impact-health%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20simple%20lifestyle%20changes%20that%20could%20cut%20the%20risk%20of%20irritable%20bowel%20syndrome%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708430040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-stomach-pain-stomach_6400348.jpg%3F20231221092438%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firritable-bowel-syndrome-the-simple-lifestyle-changes-that-could-cut-the-risk-of-developing-condition-13076143%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Simple%20everyday%20lifestyle%20changes%20could%20cut%20the%20risk%20of%20irritable%20bowel%20syndrome%20(IBS)%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20long-term%20study.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Firritable-bowel-syndrome-the-simple-lifestyle-changes-that-could-cut-the-risk-of-developing-condition-13076143%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Firritable-bowel-synd